(479, 52, 'paragraph_one', 'Platt Byard Dovell White Architects is a forty-person design firm led by Ray Dovell, Scott Duenow, James Seager, and Sam White. The firm’s practice is grounded in innovative design for new buildings, a special reputation for the design of contemporary additions to historic buildings, and a long-standing reputation for the scrupulous restoration of major historic landmarks.'),
(480, 52, '_paragraph_one', 'field_51fa6791eec1f'),
(481, 52, 'paragraph_two', 'The firm’s practice has always been grounded in the innovative designs for new buildings such as the New 42 Studios, winner of various awards, including a 2002 National AIA Honor Award. A collegial practice of partners, associates and staff, the firm has consistently delivered efficient, evocative buildings that enrich their contexts.'),
