(956, 50, 'news_field_1_copy', 'Platt Byard Dovell White Architects has been awarded an Architecture Honor Award by the American Institute of Architects, New York City Chapter for their work at the landmark New-York Historical Society.\r\n\r\nThis project was one of 13 “Honor” and 31 “Merit” projects chosen by the jury for their design quality, response to context and community, program resolution, innovation, thoughtfulness, and technique. Winning work will be exhibited in the Design Awards exhibition at the Center for Architecture from April 18 through May 31.'),
