(1094, 156, 'member_copy', 'In over twenty years practicing architecture, 11 of which have been at PBDW, Serena Losonczy has managed and designed projects in a variety of contexts with a special emphasis on educational environments. She strongly believes in the transformative power of design, collaborating closely with clients to identify and realize project goals. Her numerous institutional projects have involved both new and historic buildings, and include school such as Poly Prep, Saint David’s School, Marymount School, the Educational Alliance, Portsmouth Abbey School and Vassar College.\r\n\r\nMs. Losonczy is a member of the AIA Committee on Architecture for Education. She received her Masters of Architecture from Massachusetts Institute of Technology. '),
