(1134, 161, 'member_copy', 'I have an idea that Gatsby himself didn''t believe it would come and perhaps he no longer cared. She used to sit on the sand with his head in her lap by the hour rubbing her fingers over his eyes and looking at him with unfathomable delight. So when the blue smoke of brittle leaves was in the air and the wind blew the wet laundry stiff on the line I decided to come back home. What''s your opinion of me, anyhow? A little overwhelmed, I began the generalized evasions which that question deserves. The quiet lights in the houses were humming out into the darkness and there was a stir and bustle among the stars. I came into her room half an hour before the bridal dinner, and found her lying on her bed as lovely as the June night in her flowered dress—and as drunk as a monkey.'),
