(1800, 305, 'project_description', 'Since 1978 we have served as consulting architects to Marymount, a 650-student K-12 independent girls’ school on Manhattan’s Upper East Side. Over that period we have maintained, upgraded, and expanded the School’s three-building, 100,000 sq. ft. campus. \r\n\r\nPlatt Byard Dovell White constructed a rooftop gymnasium plus classrooms, science labs, and student spaces throughout the main building at 1026 Fifth Avenue. After our master plan quantified the extent of the need for additional space, the school acquired a townhouse at 2 East 82nd Street, which we renovated to accommodate the Middle School. Our design approach was based on retaining original detail in the public rooms of the house as elegant settings for the library and reception areas. Elements of the curriculum requiring special equipment, such as the science laboratory and the computer center, were located at the rear of the buildings. Our renovation of 2 East 82nd Street was recognized with a 2003 Lucy G. Moses Preservation Award from the New York Landmarks Conservancy.\r\n\r\nMore recently we have renovated a building at 116 East 97th Street to provide a variety of enrichment spaces to serve an enhanced curriculum.'),
