(4419, 670, 'project_description', 'These new Colonial Revival houses interpret the spirit of summer on Long Island. Organized behind a long south-facing porch, which addresses tended lawns and fine old trees, the main house accommodates large-scale entertaining as well as private family life. A welcoming stair connects living rooms to family bedrooms and a guest suite.\r\n\r\nWhen asked to design a guest house on the lot next door, we took the opportunity to provide a theater-style media room for year-round entertainment. The new structure is sited close to the road, maximizing the size and privacy of the expanded rear yard. The smaller building resembles a converted stable or garage, a congenial image that is consistent with the aria’s agricultural heritage.\r\n'),
