(4710, 714, 'member_copy', 'Anne Holford-Smith has been with PBDW for over twenty years. She has completed multiple major preservation projects for institutions, as well as master plans and new commercial buildings. She directed the firm’s award-winning work at the Cooper Union Foundation Building, the Appellate Division Courthouse and the Andrew W. Mellon Foundation, and recently completed the expansion of the Green-Wood Cemetery Chapel and the restoration of the Cemetery’s Gatehouses. She is currently designing the Moise Safra Community Center, a new, 65,000 square foot multi-purpose facility that will serve New York’s young Sephardic community.\r\nMs. Holford-Smith is a member of the New York Landmarks Conservancy and the National Trust for Historic Preservation. She received a Bachelor of Architecture from Pratt Institute.'),
