(6217, 1024, 'member_copy', 'Matthew Mueller joined PBDW in 2000. He has contributed to most of the firm’s new construction projects, including design work for the new buildings for the Reece School and the LearningSpring School, the addition of two wings to the Saginaw Art Museum, interior fit-outs for Equinox Fitness Clubs around the country, the 11-story condominium at 110th Street and Broadway, and the addition to Poly Prep’s Lower School. He is currently in charge of the design of a new mixed-use high rise development consisting of an seven-story commercial base, four stories of entertainment and 27 stories of hotel rooms, flanked by 100-foot tall LED screens, all in the heart of Times Square.\r\n\r\nMr. Mueller received his Bachelor of Architecture from Kansas State University.'),
