(6297, 1034, 'member_copy', 'In his almost fifteen years with the firm Steven Dodds has enjoyed handling some of PBDW’s more unusual work, including the installation of twelve new bells in the spire of Trinity Church, a floating boathouse in far western Ontario and a mikvah on the Upper West Side. On the more mainstream side of the practice, he served as project architect for the Reece School, the luxury condominium building at 47 East 91st Street, and the offices of the American Numismatic Society. He is currently managing or contributing to several jobs now on the boards involving residential, institutional and childcare programs, notably a new building for the Congregation Shearith Israel adjacent to the congregation’s landmark synagogue.\r\n\r\nMr. Dodds received a Bachelor of Architecture with a minor in Civil Engineering from Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute. He has authored two books and several magazine pieces.'),
