(6605, 1091, 'project_description', 'Poly Prep Lower School was the very first K-12 school in the state of New York to achieve LEED certification. It earned a Silver rating. Our design was unanimously approved by the New York City Landmarks Preservation Commission at the first hearing.\r\n\r\nPrior to its expansion, Poly Prep''s existing Prospect Park West campus was housed in the historic Hulbert Mansion, or as the students aptly named it, "the castle," with its evocative towers and turrets. PBDW designed a contemporary, but contextual, addition to the campus by successfully combining institutional use with residential scale and compact landscaping. The four-story mass was cleverly sculpted to appear no higher than two-stories from the street, so as not to dwarf either the existing historic mansion or the neighboring low-rise townhouses.\r\n\r\nThe building includes a multi-purpose room, dramatically sky-lit dance studio, dining room, homerooms for nursery through grade four, art studio, administrative offices, and a new ADA-compliant entrance to the school. The spacious, daylight-filled classrooms are specially designed with an L-shaped configuration to allow for maximum flexibility and small group learning. The landscaped playground doubles as a gathering area for the school community at the busiest times of the day, facilitating the arrival and departure of students and their parents.\r\n \r\nThis fast-track project was completed in 23 months, from programming to occupancy.'),
