(7375, 1098, 'project_description', 'In 1996 the firm was retained to prepare a Master Plan to guide capital expansion and reconfiguration of the Town School''s facilities. Working with key constituent groups, including faculty, parents and trustees, we developed a set of planning goals together with a summary of current and projected programs. As a coherent program agenda emerged, we identified planning options that addressed the School''s goals and identified a wide range of opportunities.\r\n \r\nForemost among these were a new design for the entrance to enhance the School’s presence in the community and improved circulation through the five adjacent buildings that make up the campus. We renovated the interior to create a double-height space that accommodates both the library and the computer center and articulates the School’s commitment to technology in the context of traditional resources for learning. The renovation also included classrooms for art, music, and dance, as well as improvements to the theater, gymnasium, and dining room.'),
