(7484, 1119, 'project_description', 'For forty years we were consulting architects to Saint David’s School, a 360-student independent primary school for boys on New York’s Upper East Side. We have worked with every aspect of the School’s program, focusing on renovation and adaptive reuse projects in the context of the school’s three historic townhouses.\r\n \r\nOur most recent project captured 7,500 sq. ft. of additional space from an apartment building adjacent to the principal school buildings. Within the additional space, Saint David’s was able to accommodate eight classrooms and consolidate administrative offices. A new library and technology center, science center, and expanded food services facilities were critical features of the expansion.\r\n \r\nA technically complex project, the construction entailed reframing seven stories in the apartment building to align with the floors of the adjacent school buildings, and the installation of a new elevator, stairs, and accessible entrance. Throughout the project we worked with the School to address concerns raised by the building tenants and community and to comply with the requirements of the NYC Landmarks Preservation Commission and the Building Department.\r\n \r\nWe are currently in design for a renovation of the entire apartment building to house two gymnasiums, a 250-seat performance space, a dining room, and classrooms.'),
