(7921, 1175, 'project_description', 'This new structure is a nine-story condominium tower in the Central Park West Historic District attached to the Congregation’s historic synagogue.  The mixed-use development combines five floors of apartments with a community center in the lower four floors, plus below-grade space for banquets, kitchens, and support spaces.\r\n\r\nThe ground floor will accommodate a new entrance to the historic sanctuary plus a multi-purpose space for synagoge events. Upstairs, the building’s community space will include classrooms, offices, event and meeting rooms, and space for the congregation’s extensive historic archives and artifacts dating from the 17th Century.\r\n\r\nThe New York City Landmarks Preservation Commission recently voted unanimously to approve the design by Platt Byard Dovell White for an addition to the existing synagogue, and commended it as an appropriate, harmonious addition to the district and the individual landmark.'),
