(8031, 1192, 'project_description', 'When dancer Michiel Baryshnikov purchased a large property in this curious enclave overlooking the Hudson River he was looking for a venue appropriate to his position and stature in the world of the arts. The property came with an existing house that was suitable for large-scale entertaining. He commissioned this new design for a small cabin to create a personal retreat from those very activities that would take place next door. \r\nThe large house has since been sold, but Baryshnikov has retained the smaller structure as his personal dacha.'),
