(8834, 1286, 'member_copy', 'Kathryn Whitman has an unusual range of institutional, commercial and residential projects, including new construction, adaptive reuse and interior design. In her fifteen years with PBDW, she has managed the addition to and renovation of the Andrew W. Mellon Foundation on East 61st Street, alterations for the Residence of the Japanese Ambassador to the United Nations, and designs for a number of private houses. She has worked on academic renovation projects for Barnard College and Fordham University.\r\n\r\nMs. Whitman received a Bachelor of Architecture from Cooper Union and a Bachelor of Arts from Mount Holyoke College.'),
